1. Ja *penim* pismo svaki dan. (I write a letter every day.)
2. On *peni* pesmu o ljubavi. (He composes a love song.)
3. Mi *penimo* zajedno na karaokeu. (We sing together at karaoke.)
4. Vi *penite* za svečanu priliku. (You sing for a formal occasion.)
5. Oni *penju* po drveću u parku. (They climb trees in the park.)
6. Mačka *peni* jer želi hranu. (The cat meows because it wants food.)
7. Pas *peni* na prolaznike. (The dog barks at passersby.)
8. Trgovac *peni* cenu na pijaci. (The vendor haggles the price at the market.)
9. Studenti *penju* stepenice do fakulteta. (The students climb the stairs to the university.)
10. On *peni* užurbano na kompjuteru. (He types quickly on the computer.)

Note: The word "peni" in Serbian can have multiple meanings and can be used in various forms. In these sentences, I have provided different meanings and forms of the word to showcase its versatility.